  "name": "RPlog_Tacuba_the_Hutt_s_Flying_Circus",
  "title": "Clowns and Chaos in Mos Espa",
  "summary": "Tacuba the Hutt's Flying Circus arrives in the Mos Espa spaceport, its garish disco-ball palanquin, caged monkey-lizards, frog-dogs, drummers, and clowns drawing crowds and attracting the wary attention of Tatooine's warlord Johanna, who watches from the mayor's office above the plaza. Among the onlookers are the Sith Crestian Tarasar and his sharp-tongued daughter Atsvara, the smuggler Axel Vichten escorting a strange clawed child given to him by the Imperator, and the warrior Kipran with his beloved, the Imperium Crown Princess Sonja. When an escaped frog-dog overturns a vendor's cart, a circus aide smooths things over with credits, robbing Axel of an excuse for violence. A clown later gets too close to Axel, whose mechanical hand discharges and blasts the performer across the square; Axel is promptly tackled and arrested by Johanna's constables, who keep him and his demented droid R2-FU under standing watch. A circus barker tries to recruit Sonja and then Kipran for the troupe, provoking Kipran's protective ire and Sonja's teasing, while Tacuba announces a partnership with the upcoming Mos Espa races. The scene closes with the carnival's spectacle continuing, Axel hauled off, and Crestian resolving to bail out his arrested flag officer before the races.",
